comments:
Transferred from Lincolnshire to the county of Parts of Holland 
    on 1.4.1889. See also Table 2, note (c).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Fletton within the borough of 
    Peterborough became part of the Soke of Peterborough. The parish was abolished 
    1894 to become the separate parishes of Fletton Urban and Fletton Rural.

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Peterborough unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (j).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Fletton. See 
    also Table 2, note (b).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Fletton in Peterborough 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.
Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.

Created 1.11.1908 out of the parish of Peterborough Without. Abolished 
    1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.
Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.
Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.

Created 1.4.1929 from the parishes of Peterborough Within, Fletton 
    Urban, Peterborough Without, Woodstone Urban, Walton, Werrington, Longthorpe, 
    Paston, Minster Close Precincts and Gunthorpe. Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Peterborough unparished area. See also Table 2, notes (f) and 
    (g).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of St. John the Baptist 
    in Peterborough Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the 
    parish of Peterborough.

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of St. John the 
    Baptist. Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Peterborough 
    Within and Peterborough Without.

Abolished 1.10.1905 to become the separate parishes of Stanground 
    North and Stanground South, in Isle of Ely and Huntingdonshire respectively. See also Table 2, note (a).

Created 1.10.1905 from the Isle of Ely part of the parish of Stanground. 
    See also Table 2, notes (e) and (i).

Created 1.10.1905 from the Huntingdonshire part of the parish 
    of Stanground. Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Peterborough unparished area. See also Table 2, notes (b) and 
    (j).
Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.
Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.

Abolished 1.4.1974 and added to the Peterborough unparished area. See also Table 2, note 
    (j).

In 1889 the part of the parish of Woodstone within the borough 
    of Peterborough became part of the Soke of Peterborough. Abolished 
    1894 to become the separate parishes of Woodstone Urban and Woodstone Rural, 
    in the Soke of Peterborough and Huntingdonshire respectively..

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Woodstone. See 
    also Table 2, note (b).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Woodstone in Peterborough 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1929 and added to the parish of Peterborough.
